text: Viktor Drago wonder why his father stayed in a vodka induced slumber and was at times very abusive to himself and his mother until one day his mother put in his hand an old dusty VHS tape marked " For my son " and it was then that for the first time in his young 12 year old life he saw a side of his father he'd never seen before... Once A Captain of the Red Army, A decorated war veteran, the absolute embodiment of Neitzche's philosophy in both mind and body. A proud man that loved his family and Mother Russia and would very well give his life for either had fallen from grace at the hands of an American. After viewing hours of footage of this unique side of his father he walked away with tears streaming down and having a new found of respect for his father. He swore vengeance on the one that brought his father and family to this lowly state of human existence. At that very moment he vowed to pick up the torch and restore the sir name of Drago back to its former glory! Fastforward 12 years and Viktor Drago is 24 years old and an undefeated boxing champion in his own right but his fight is not for money or fame... No... It is quite simply a child that is trying to have a connection with his father.

text: So Adonis is a light heavyweight fighter, and Drago looks like he outweighs him by 40 lbs.  Interested to see how they are going to play that one off.  Maybe Adonis jumps up to heavyweight?  I think this movie will be just fine.  But when I heard Dolph Lundgren was coming back, I totally had a storyline in my head, in which a sick Rocky dies in the middle of the movie, and Drago comes out of the woodwork and offers to train Adonis to fight whomever the main opponent for the movie would have been.  It would have been such a moral conflict.  This seems more like Rocky 3, 2.0.  It sort of goes against how Rocky IV actually ended, with Rocky and Drago seemingly finding mutual respect for each other.  Still look forward to seeing it!

text: Seen this film twice now, and freaking loved it both times. Really awesome film. Go see it. You know I‚Äôve already started thinking about what they should do for Creed 3 (which I really hope they make) and i don‚Äôt mean like all the silly comments Creed vs Clubber Lang‚Äôs son or daughter or anything like that. I‚Äôve been thinking how can they step it up emotionally? Because this an incredibly emotional film, like most of the Rocky movies, it‚Äôs a character Drama as much as a Boxing film, and here we have a really good reason for it to because I mean Adonis is facing the son of the man who killed his Father. Now how do we level up from that? How about this, what if we find out that Donny‚Äôs mother had another son, not with Apollo, but with another man, and this Son got lost in the system whereas we know Donny got rescued by Mary Anne. So here we have this long lost brother, who see‚Äôs his little brother basically renouncing their mother‚Äôs name, and sitting pretty with a wife, kid, new mom, and new surrogate father in Rocky, so now this resentment is starting to build, so he works and works and works to challenge Adonis for the Heavyweight title in an effort to break him down and take away the things that matter most to him. Boom! I‚Äôve solved Creed 3!
